article.headline: North Dakota 27, N. Colorado 25
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Zeb Miller kicked a career best 54-yard field goal with 1:52 left, lifting North Dakota to a 27-25 victory over struggling Northern Colorado on Saturday. Brent Goska completed 18 of 30 passes for 206 yards and a touchdown and ran for a second for North Dakota (5-3). Miller also had a 41-yard field goal. Ross Brenneman recovered two fumbles for the Fighting Sioux, who evened the all-time series at 12-12. Patrick Walker caught 10 passes, two for touchdowns, and a school and Big Sky record 315 yards for the Bears (0-9).
